      <bioghist id="aspace_b89cb912dd6bced17599033e9c64e596">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Martin Sebastian Soria was born in Berlin, Germany, on July 3, 1911. He received a B.A. degree from the University of Madrid, and M.A. and Ph.D. degrees from Harvard. Soria also studied at the University of Zurich. He was an instructor at Princeton from 1944-1946, and a member of the art department at Michigan State University from 1948 until his death in Brussels on February 15, 1961.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_7ca741b19b1ca3b7f89747019a8267ed">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The papers consist of photographs, correspondence, research notes, and clippings assembled by art historian Martin Soria and documenting his studies of art and architecture in Europe, particularly Spain.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_67f5e715d8e757b4b296a55a11e40174">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>Preliminary box listing only.</p>  
      </arrangement>
