      <dsc>
         <c id="ref11" level="series">
            <did>
               <unittitle>Box listing</unittitle>
            </did>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_f2250dc2e2e81dd4741f1269b09272fb">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Folders 1-167 consist of items, primarily photographs, which were individually numbered and indexed by Martin Soria. Although photographs comprise the bulk of the material, other items, such as correspondence, notes, and printed material, have been included and are numbered and indexed. Additional research files and visual resources are found in boxes 9-11.</p>
            </scopecontent>
            <arrangement id="aspace_dd88cb635a8d490f32a8d299008f194e">
               <head>Arrangement</head>
               <p>The photographs in folders 1-106 are arranged by artist and can be accessed by referring to the index prepared under the direction of George Kubler. Artists are listed alphabetically. Each entry consists of the name of the artist, birth and death dates, origin and school, folder number, and photograph number. Material in these folders may also be accessed by utilizing a two page school of painting index. A detailed list of the photographs is included in most of the folders.</p>
               <p>The contents of folders 107-167 were originally housed in four letter boxes labeled A-D. The items were removed from the letter boxes and foldered. A separate index exists for these folders. The index consists of the photograph number, title of work or a short description of the item, artist, location, and notes. Each page of the index corresponds to one folder. The contents of folders 107-116, originally housed in letter box A, did not have a detailed listing, and therefore, broad folder titles were used for identification. Folders 117-166 have detailed listings as described above. Folder 167 contains unidentified contents.</p>
            </arrangement>
